	4. A lunch break while working construction jobs at the age of 21 proved p
	ivotal to his career as it was then that he fell in love with the King of 
	Rock & Roll. Toki often spent his breaks at Tower Records and one day\, El
	vis ’56 ruled the store’s TVs. So mesmerized was Toki\, that he only retur
	ned to his job when the foreman bought him the VHS tape so he would leave 
	the store. The rest was history!\n\nToki made his inaugural international 
	performance back in 2007 at The Cavern Bar in Dallas\, TX to a packed hous
	e\, and found his calling. He has returned almost every year to perform in
	 numerous cities across the US and all over the world!\n\nOn top of his Gr
	aceland achievement\, Toki has won many global competitions\, including as
	 the first foreigner to win the famed Branson contest in 2023 and a previo
	us victory in Parkes\, Australia. He has been featured in the New York Tim
	es\, Reuters\, and many more world-wide publications.\n\nNow focused on ke
	eping Elvis’ memory alive across the globe\, Toki may not speak English\, 
